From ca68d8c427d6654a73e018ab85d6191d6bfb191e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Denys Fedoryshchenko <denys.f@collabora.com>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 14:56:26 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] vlan_mon: bind ETH_P_ALL packet handler to init_net on
 kernels >= 6.6

The vlan_mon driver registers a global packet_type with type=ETH_P_ALL
to intercept PADI/IP/ARP frames before they reach the protocol stack.
Since Linux 6.6 every ETH_P_ALL packet_type needs either dev or
af_packet_net set. Bind the handler to init_net, which matches the
driver's existing behaviour.

Upstream: https://github.com/accel-ppp/accel-ppp/commit/ca68d8c427d6654a73e018ab85d6191d6bfb191e
Signed-off-by: Denys Fedoryshchenko <denys.f@collabora.com>
[backport to ACCEL-PPP 1.14.0]
Signed-off-by: Abdulkader Alrezej <alrazj.abdulkader@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/vlan_mon/vlan_mon.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/vlan_mon/vlan_mon.c
+++ b/drivers/vlan_mon/vlan_mon.c
@@ -753,6 +753,9 @@ static int __init vlan_mon_init(void)
 	}
 #endif
 
+#if LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(6,6,0)
+	vlan_pt.af_packet_net = &init_net;
+#endif
 	dev_add_pack(&vlan_pt);
 
 	return 0;
